{'id': 1366887, 'body': 'Please be informed that as of the April 2016 release of SCRUFF v5.011 and after extensive analysis of usage trends, we have suspended support for and further development of the SCRUFF extension for Apple Watch. This allows us to maintain our focus on delivering a best-in-class experience on iPhone and iPad.

We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. Please note, however, that you will still be able to receive and respond to SCRUFF notifications on Apple Watch.

If you'd like to speak with us directly, you can navigate to the Settings menu within SCRUFF and select "Contact SCRUFF Support", or submit a ticket to our support team by visiting support.scruff.com. WOOF!', 'modified': '2017-09-26T20:43:47Z'}

{'id': 21403656, 'body': 'We‚Äôre sorry if connectivity errors are preventing you from logging in. If you receive an error message regarding your email address or password, follow the steps for resetting your password via email.

After running diagnostics, a red or yellow dot may indicate an issue with your current connection on either Wi-Fi or with mobile data. Try switching to the other method to see if that resolves the issue.

If you are still unable to connect, please visit support.scruff.com and submit a ticket so our support team can get you connected (and WOOFing) again.', 'modified': '2021-03-02T17:11:48Z'}

